      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":15,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"sunday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest day. Let your body absorb the week ahead. Gentle walking or light stretching is totally fine if you feel like moving.\"},\"monday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day. Use this time to prep your gear, hydrate well, and get good sleep — these habits matter as much as the runs.\"},\"tuesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run, 20–25 min at 7:00–8:00/km. This should feel conversational — if you can't chat, slow down. Building your aerobic base starts here.\"},\"wednesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day between your run days. Recovery is when your body actually gets stronger — this day is doing important work.\"},\"thursday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run, 20–25 min at 7:00–8:00/km. Same relaxed effort as Tuesday. Notice how your breathing feels — it should stay easy throughout.\"},\"friday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day before your long run. A short walk is fine, but save your energy for Saturday.\"},\"saturday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"Long run, 30–35 min at 7:00–8:00/km. This is your longest effort of the week. Go slow, stay easy, and enjoy the time on your feet — distance and time matter more than pace right now.\"},\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to Week 1, Sarah! This first week is all about establishing your rhythm with three runs at a comfortable, conversational pace. Your current base of 15 km/week is a solid starting point, and we're going to build on it steadily and safely. Every run this week should feel easy — almost like you could go longer but you're choosing not to. That restraint is actually a coaching skill, and it pays off in the weeks ahead. The most important thing this week is simply showing up and finishing each run feeling good.\"}"
        }
      ]
    }
